# --- AI provider ---
# The AI report can use any of three providers (pick in the UI):
#   1. Local Claude   — if you're logged in to the Claude CLI on this machine,
#                       CommitArc reuses that session (billed to your Claude
#                       subscription). No key needed. Nothing to set here.
#   2. Server key     — set ANTHROPIC_API_KEY below.
#   3. GUI key        — paste a key in the app (stored only in your browser).
#
# Optional Claude API key (used by providers 2 above). Get one at
# https://console.anthropic.com/
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=

# Optional: override where the local Claude credentials live (defaults to
# ~/.claude, the OS keychain, etc. — auto-detected).
# CLAUDE_DIR=

# Optional. A GitHub personal access token used for PUBLIC repos and as a
# higher rate-limit fallback. For PRIVATE repos the app prefers the `gh` CLI
# (see README), but a token with `repo` scope here also works.
# Create one at https://github.com/settings/tokens
GITHUB_TOKEN=
